parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to unintended airbag deployment, which can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities. Additionally, the failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash can also lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag deploys without warning
the airbag does not deploy in the event of a crash
the seatbelt tightens unexpectedly
the airbag sensor light flickers
and the vehicle crashes or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the SRS system warning light can indicate a potential failure of the airbag system, which can lead to unintended airbag deployment or failure to deploy in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The SRS system warning light illuminates
the airbag warning light flashes
and the airbag sensor light flickers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts to repair the airbag system can lead to a delay in repairs, leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.
symptoms: The dealer is unable to obtain the necessary parts to repair the airbag system
and the manufacturer is unable to provide a timeline for when the parts will be available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without warning
and may not respond to braking attempts. This can occur while driving in forward or reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Erratic acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates erratically
often with a sudden jerk or lurch
and may not respond consistently to accelerator pedal input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck accelerator pedal can lead to unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes stuck or stuck in a partially depressed position
causing the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column upper bracket can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to maneuver, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the steering wheel makes a strange noise when turning
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become extremely difficult to maneuver, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel makes a strange noise when turning
the power steering system fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the brakes do not respond
the steering system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission system can cause the vehicle to lose power and momentum, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle loses power and momentum.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag and seatbelt pretensioner system can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to potential injuries.
symptoms: The airbag deploys unexpectedly
the seatbelt pretensioner fails to deploy.
